  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In 2003, at the height of the AIDS crisis in Uganda, Canon Gideon Byamugisha, an international AIDS activist, responded to a desperate need for vocational training and social support among orphaned and vulnerable youth by establishing the Hope Institute for Transformational Leadership and Development. Since then, 3,000 youth have been educated to be skilled leaders in their communities. The Institute&apos;s fully accredited, holistic program includes sports, music, health and community engagement.</narrative>
  </description>
